---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { impressum } from '../config/impressum';

const lastUpdated = 'April 8, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Legal Notice (Impressum)"
  description="Legal notice and provider information for Haseeb Studio Blog (Germany)."
>
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-bold text-surface-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
      Legal Notice <span class="text-surface-500 dark:text-surface-400 text-3xl md:text-4xl font-normal">(Impressum)</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-surface-500 dark:text-surface-400 mb-10">
      Last updated: {lastUpdated}
    </p>

    <div class="prose text-surface-700 dark:text-surface-300">
      <p class="text-lg not-italic">
        This page provides legally required provider information for visitors in Germany
        (<em>Impressum</em>, under the German Telemedia Act (TMG)). The site content is in English;
        this notice is provided in English for clarity.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl">Information pursuant to Section 5 TMG</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-surface-600 dark:text-surface-400 not-italic">
        (German Telemedia Act — <span lang="de">Telemediengesetz</span>)
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>{impressum.name}</strong>
        <br />
        {impressum.street}
        <br />
        {impressum.postalCode} {impressum.city}
        <br />
        {impressum.country}
      </p>
      {impressum.businessNote && (
        <p>
          <em>{impressum.businessNote}</em>
        </p>
      )}
      {impressum.vatId && (
        <p>
          VAT identification number pursuant to Section 27a of the German VAT Act (UStG):{' '}
          <strong>{impressum.vatId}</strong>
        </p>
      )}

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Email: <a href={`mailto:${impressum.email}`}>{impressum.email}</a>
        {impressum.phone && (
          <>
            <br />
            Phone: {impressum.phone}
          </>
        )}
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl">Responsible for content (Section 55(2) RStV)</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-surface-600 dark:text-surface-400 not-italic">
        (German Interstate Broadcasting Treaty — <span lang="de">Rundfunkstaatsvertrag</span>)
      </p>
      <p>
        {impressum.name}
        <br />
        {impressum.street}, {impressum.postalCode} {impressum.city}
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl">Liability for content</h2>
      <p>
        As a service provider under Section 7(1) TMG, we are responsible for our own content on these
        pages in accordance with general law. However, under Sections 8 to 10 TMG, we are not
        obliged as a service provider to monitor transmitted or stored third-party information or to
        investigate circumstances indicating illegal activity.
      </p>
      <p>
        Obligations to remove or block the use of information under general law remain unaffected.
        Liability in this respect is only possible from the time we become aware of a specific
        infringement. If we become aware of such infringements, we will remove the content
        immediately.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl">Liability for links</h2>
      <p>
        Our site contains links to external third-party websites whose content we cannot influence.
        Therefore we cannot guarantee or assume liability for those external contents. The respective
        provider or operator of the linked pages is always responsible for their content. The linked
        pages were checked for possible legal violations at the time the link was created. Unlawful
        content was not recognizable at that time.
      </p>
      <p>
        Permanent monitoring of linked pages without concrete evidence of a violation is not
        reasonable. If we become aware of violations, we will remove such links immediately.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl">Copyright</h2>
      <p>
        Content and works created by the site operator on these pages are subject to German
        copyright law. Duplication, processing, distribution, or any use beyond the limits of
        copyright require the written consent of the respective author or creator. Downloads and
        copies of this site are permitted only for private, non-commercial use.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl">Online dispute resolution</h2>
      <p>
        The European Commission provides a platform for online dispute resolution (ODR):{' '}
        <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">
          https://ec.europa.eu/consumers/odr/
        </a>
        . Our email address is listed above under Contact.
      </p>
      <p>
        We are not willing or obliged to participate in dispute resolution proceedings before a
        consumer arbitration board.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
